# Cursor / AI assistant rules — wiamlabs-web

This repo is **wiamlabs.com** only — the public WiamLabs company site
(about, products, news, careers, press, and now per-product pricing).
It is not any individual product's own site — WiamApp's marketing site,
WiamPass's web app, and WiamTrade each live in their own separate repo.

## Stack (this repo only)
- **Next.js 15** App Router, TypeScript
- Hosting: **Vercel** (not Render — this repo deploys differently
  from WiamApp/WiamPass, which are Render services)
- Content: static JSON in `content/` (`products.json`, `news.json`) as
  a fallback, with an optional CMS layer (`lib/cms.ts`) that pulls from
  `wiamlabs-studio`'s API when configured
- Email: **Brevo**, not Resend — Resend's free tier is already used by
  WiamApp on the same domain-verification limit, so this repo uses a
  separate provider on purpose

## URL structure — read this before adding routes
Each product gets a **top-level** route, not nested under `/products/`:
```
wiamlabs.com/wiamapp/pricing
wiamlabs.com/wiampass/pricing
wiamlabs.com/wiamtrade/pricing
```
implemented as the single dynamic route `app/[product]/pricing/page.tsx`,
driven by `lib/products.ts` + `content/products.json`. Do not create
per-product static folders (`app/wiamapp/`, `app/wiampass/`) — add the
product to `products.json` instead, the dynamic route already covers it.

The existing `app/products/[slug]/page.tsx` (product overview/pitch
page) is separate and stays where it is — pricing and overview are two
different routes by design, not duplicates.

Static top-level routes (`about`, `careers`, `contact`, `news`, `media`,
`press`, `products`, `legal`) take priority over the `[product]`
dynamic segment at build time — never rename a product to match one of
these words.

## Shared Paystack webhook router
`app/api/webhook/paystack/route.ts` is the ONE webhook URL the shared
WiamLabs Paystack account is limited to. It verifies the signature,
reads `metadata.app` from the event, and forwards to that product's
real backend (`WIAMAPP_WEBHOOK_URL`, `WIAMPASS_WEBHOOK_URL`, etc. —
server-side env vars, never `NEXT_PUBLIC_`). Untagged events (all of
WiamPass's transactions predate this convention) fall back to
WiamPass on purpose — never remove that fallback without confirming
WiamPass tags its own transactions first. This route replaces the
standalone `wiamlabs-payments-router` service — that repo is
deprecated, do not deploy it, everything lives here now.

## Hard rules
- Pricing numbers in `content/products.json` marked
  `"billingNote": "PLACEHOLDER — ..."` are NOT real prices. Never
  remove that field or treat the accompanying price as final without
  being told the real number.
- Don't add authentication or a dashboard here — that's
  `wiamlabs-studio`'s job, a separate repo.
